begin_memory_text: In the beginning we were struggling to figure out topics to talk about and I think we misheard each other initially. We exchanged basic information and opened with talk about what's for dinner, what hobbies we've taken up, etc. There were more lulls then.
middle_memory_text: Towards the middle we got into a better flow. I got her to open up a bit more about her hobbies and interests. We talked about walking, fitness, etc. and the topic of pets came up. I learned she had three cats. I didn't have any so I could only talk so much but I got a better picture of who she was.
end_memory_text: We were able to sustain conversation more towards the end. We chatted about what vacation you would take if you could go any place, any time. I answered in a more traditional way and she brought up more fantastical scenarios like seeing the pyramids being built or seeing dinosaurs. I reconsidered my answers in light of this and we talked along that line. The topic of technology and tracking of information came up towards the very end.
rest_of_day_open: The coming week should be good. I have some cooking projects I wanted to work on since I came across some decent cuts of meat. I will try using a tagine I've had in storage as well and see how it goes. Otherwise things will be pretty mundane, just the usual watching stuff and getting groceries, cleaning etc.
critical_positive: I think that while the other person was not necessarily willing to take the lead in conversation much, they were ok with me doing so and I don't mind stepping up if there is a void. I also think they were ok with stretching a topic more and cared more about the feelings of a topic than the information so that gave me some room to feel out where to transition.
critical_negative: We didn't have too much in common so we had to stretch some other topics that were in the middle. I think that it would be difficult to get them to open up more without a good path of topics, so in some sense I was lucky to even get as far as I did.

middle_memory_text: We talked about why he did not have any pets and how he felt about caged pets. Also what kind of hobbies we enjoyed doing him manly fixing things and odd jobs around the house.
end_memory_text: We talked about if we could do time travel were would you want to end up and why, brought us right into talking about robots and transformers. About how he used to play with them when he was a kid.
rest_of_day_open: Well tomorrow is the start of a new week, an i already had to cancel some plans since its supposed to rain most of the week. Other then that i see my week going alright since i have to run errands and take care of some personal things for my family.
